s...What makes a good one?</span><hr size=1> Twisting while performing crowd control makes a good bard.  Nothing bothers me more than a bard in my group doing nothing but keeping one mob mezzed.  I'd just as soon root park something and have the bard doing something else.<br><br>stymp mcstump <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nydia>Nydia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/11/02 8:32:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=812.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bards...What makes a good one?</span><hr size=1> Crowd control is nice, especially if there's no chanter around, but I'd have to agree with Briannae on this one.  I recently grouped with a bard friend in Frenzy, and since there was both a chanter and bard in the party, we did an experiment: first she tried twisting 2-3 songs and fighting, as she usually does; then, she decided to stop fighting altogether and just swap instruments as appropriate and twist 4 songs (at L 45, 1st is just going down as she gets 4th off).  Result: The melees were frigging lawnmowers, and the cleric and I *never* ran low on mana.  It was amazing, and we killed significantly faster than when she was meleeing, dual procing weapons or no.  You'd have to ask her exactly what she was twisting (believe it was Psalm of Shielding, Berzerker Crescendo, and Cantata of Soothing plus Chains during the fights) and when, but we both learned something that evening...  <br><br>Regards,<br>Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>Autonomous Collective<br><br>P.S. Her name is Phallen if you're of the 45ish persuasion and are looking for a good bard... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoti