ree most important keys to being a bard are:<br><br>1) Knowledge - know what your songs will do and just what they won't.  This includes knowing how your songs stack with other classes.  Little things like, can enchanters overwrite this mezz?; will this song break mezz?; will this song pull aggro off the tanks?  This is by far the most important thing.<br><br>2) Adaptability - be versatile and ready to fill any role in a group, and change that role as the group dynamics demand it.<br><br>3) Awareness - more than any other class except perhaps clerics and enchanters, know what is happening around the current mob the group is beating on.  Yes, it is hard to type while twisting three or four songs, but sometimes the one or two seconds warning you might give will keep the 'chanter and cleric alive long enough to prevent disaster.<br><br><br><br> <p>Marilana Valeris<BR>Minstrel of the First Ballad<BR>Ayonae Ro Server<BR>Proud member of Prism<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubriaanae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Briaanae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/12/02 7:53:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=812.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://brianastearns.homestead.com/files/pinkie.gif WIDTH=33 HEIGHT=128></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What makes a good bard.</span><hr size=1> Marilana is by far my favorite bard...in and out of game. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><