 you a good bard. Crowd control... That is just being high enough level and having good charisma. You can teach a monkey to do that if they know how to switch targets. <br><br>From what I am reading most of the people posting here are not bards and dont really have a true understanding of the class.<br><br>Oh and btw not much Crowd control a bard is gonna do at a ToV raid. <p>Cuthbert DirgewielderEl Virtuoso and Uber Geek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umaximillianvondrakov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximillian vonDrakov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/13/02 6:56:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=812.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What makes a good bard.</span><hr size=1> What's a bard?<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uscratch2k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scratch2k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/13/02 2:14:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=812.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What makes a good bard.</span><hr size=1> Too much emphasis is being put on crowd control and twisting. I 100% agree with Cuthbert on this one, a good bard is one that knows what to play and when, whether it's just one song or they're trying to give themselves cramps playing 3-4 songs for hours on end, either way, it's knowing the situation and adapting to it.<br><br>With over 60 songs, that's not always easy and the bard that can decide which ones to use, and when, is going to be a hellova bard.<br><br>In groups, I'll often play nothing but mana song for hours, for the sole reason that if I tried to twist the 3-4 songs I'd *like* to twist in that situation I'd not only lose my mind, but lost use of my hands for a week after the session. Nothing wrong with a single song twist I say, don't be afraid of it! <p><A target=_blank HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51151><IMG border=0 SRC="http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/EddeeSig3.jpg"></A></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showMessageRange?topicID=812.topic&start=21&stop=37>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=812.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=812.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=812.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=812.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.threadControl?topicID=812.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator